00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:47,195
Oh, Ian, thank you so much.

521
00:18:47,229 --> 00:18:49,163
It's great.
Now throw it out.

522
00:18:49,198 --> 00:18:51,165
I need a new one,
and I need it in 20 minutes.

523
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,166
Ugh.

524
00:18:52,201 --> 00:18:53,241
Look, if you didn't want

525
00:18:53,268 --> 00:18:55,002
to be on call 24-7
for emergencies,

526
00:18:55,037 --> 00:18:56,704
then you should not have gone
into the high-stakes world

527
00:18:56,738 --> 00:18:57,905
of banner making!

528
00:19:00,193 --> 00:19:01,514
What the hell is all this about?

529
00:19:01,528 --> 00:19:03,329
You'll see.

530
00:19:03,363 --> 00:19:05,431
Well, I got to say,

531
00:19:05,465 --> 00:19:07,134
that was a heck of a lot of fun.

532
00:19:09,521 --> 00:19:10,628
What on Earth?

533
00:19:10,748 --> 00:19:13,435
Happy Inauguration Day, buddy.

534
00:19:13,685 --> 00:19:15,634
Oh, jeez, Leslie.

535
00:19:38,312 --> 00:19:41,414
The passing of our beloved Mayor Gunderson

536
00:19:41,534 --> 00:19:43,660
marks the end of an era.

537
00:19:43,969 --> 00:19:46,377
But we are about to begin a new chapter

538
00:19:46,497 --> 00:19:47,880
in Pawnee's history.

539
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,321
Ladies and gentlemen,

540
00:19:49,441 --> 00:19:52,939
the new mayor of the great city of
Pawnee, Indiana,

541
00:19:53,059 --> 00:19:54,196
Garry Gergich.

542
00:19:55,535 --> 00:19:57,749
I just want to say...

543
00:20:06,134 --> 00:20:07,834
I'm flying!

